  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "id": "a9",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": ["### 2.6 Genre Co-occurrence Heatmap"]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": null,
   "id": "b7",
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "co_matrix = df[GENRE_COLS].T.dot(df[GENRE_COLS])\n",
    "co_matrix.index = GENRE_LABELS\n",
    "co_matrix.columns = GENRE_LABELS\n",
    "# Zero out diagonal for clarity\n",
    "np.fill_diagonal(co_matrix.values, 0)\n",
    "\n",
    "fig, ax = plt.subplots(figsize=(14, 12))\n",
    "fig.patch.set_facecolor('#0d0d1a')\n",
    "sns.heatmap(\n",
    "    co_matrix, ax=ax,\n",
    "    cmap='magma', linewidths=0.3,\n",
    "    annot=True, fmt='.0f', annot_kws={'size': 7},\n",
    "    cbar_kws={'label': 'Co-occurrence Count'}\n",
    ")\n",
    "ax.set_title('Genre Co-occurrence Heatmap', fontsize=15, fontweight='bold')\n",
    "plt.xticks(rotation=45, ha='right', fontsize=8)\n",
    "plt.yticks(rotation=0, fontsize=8)\n",
    "plt.tight_layout()\n",
    "plt.savefig('eda_genre_cooccurrence.png', dpi=120, bbox_inches='tight')\n",
    "plt.show()"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "id": "c1",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "## 3. Weighted Cosine Similarity Model\n",
    "\n",
    "### How it works\n",
    "\n",
    "Each anime is represented as a feature vector combining:\n",
    "- **Genre vector** (28 binary dimensions) × `genre_weight` (default 0.7)\n",
    "- **Normalized rating** (rate/5.0) × `(1 - genre_weight)` (default 0.3)\n",
    "\n",
    "The final recommendation score:\n",
    "$$\\text{score}(A, B) = \\frac{\\vec{v}_A \\cdot \\vec{v}_B}{\\|\\vec{v}_A\\| \\|\\vec{v}_B\\|}$$\n",
    "\n",
    "Where $\\vec{v}_i = [\\text{genre\\_weight} \\cdot \\text{genres}_i \\;|\;\\text{rating\\_weight} \\cdot \\hat{r}_i]$\n",
    "\n",
    "**Why weighted?** Pure genre cosine similarity treats all matching anime equally regardless of quality. Adding a rating dimension biases results toward well-received titles within the same genre cluster."
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": null,
   "id": "c2",
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "# ── Preprocessing ──\n",
    "df_model = df[df['votes'] >= 50].reset_index(drop=True).copy()\n",
    "df_model[GENRE_COLS] = df_model[GENRE_COLS].fillna(0.0)\n",
    "df_model['rate'] = pd.to_numeric(df_model['rate'], errors='coerce').fillna(0.0)\n",
    "print(f'Modelling pool: {len(df_model)} anime (votes ≥ 50)')"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": null,
   "id": "c3",
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "def build_feature_matrix(df_in, genre_cols, genre_weight=0.7):\n",
    "    \"\"\"Weighted feature matrix: genre + normalized rating.\"\"\"\n",
    "    genre_matrix = df_in[genre_cols].values.astype(float) * genre_weight\n",
    "    norm_rate = (df_in['rate'].values / 5.0).reshape(-1, 1) * (1 - genre_weight)\n",
    "    return np.hstack([genre_matrix, norm_rate])\n",
    "\n",
    "matrix_07 = build_feature_matrix(df_model, GENRE_COLS, genre_weight=0.7)\n",
    "print(f'Feature matrix shape: {matrix_07.shape}')  # (N_anime, 29)"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": null,
   "id": "c4",
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "# Compute full similarity matrix\n",
    "sim_matrix = cosine_similarity(matrix_07)\n",
    "print(f'Similarity matrix shape: {sim_matrix.shape}')\n",
    "# Peek at most similar pairs\n",
    "np.fill_diagonal(sim_matrix, 0)  # zero self-similarity\n",
    "top_pairs = np.unravel_index(np.argsort(sim_matrix, axis=None)[-10:], sim_matrix.shape)\n",
    "print('\\nTop 5 most similar pairs:')\n",
    "for i, j in zip(*[x[::-1][:5] for x in top_pairs]):\n",
    "    print(f'  {df_model.iloc[i][\"anime\"]}  <-->  {df_model.iloc[j][\"anime\"]}  |  sim={sim_matrix[i,j]:.4f}')"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "id": "c5",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": ["### 3.1 Recommendation Functions"]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": null,
   "id": "c6",
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "def recommend_by_title(anime_name, df_in, matrix, genre_cols, top_n=10):\n",
    "    \"\"\"Return top_n similar anime given a title.\"\"\"\n",
    "    matches = df_in[df_in['anime'] == anime_name]\n",
    "    if matches.empty:\n",
    "        print(f'Anime \"{anime_name}\" not found in the filtered pool.')\n",
    "        return pd.DataFrame()\n",
    "    idx = matches.index[0]\n",
    "    sims = cosine_similarity([matrix[idx]], matrix)[0]\n",
    "    sim_scores = sorted(enumerate(sims), key=lambda x: x[1], reverse=True)\n",
    "    sim_scores = [(i, s) for i, s in sim_scores if i != idx][:top_n]\n",
    "    recs = df_in.iloc[[i for i, _ in sim_scores]][['anime','rate','votes','episodes']].copy()\n",
    "    recs['similarity_%'] = [round(s * 100, 2) for _, s in sim_scores]\n",
    "    return recs.reset_index(drop=True)\n",
    "\n",
    "\n",
    "def recommend_by_genres(selected_genre_labels, df_in, genre_cols, genre_labels, genre_weight=0.7, top_n=10):\n",
    "    \"\"\"Return top_n anime based on selected genre labels.\"\"\"\n",
    "    query_vec = np.zeros(len(genre_cols) + 1)\n",
    "    for i, col in enumerate(genre_cols):\n",
    "        label = col.replace('genre_', '').replace('-', ' ').title()\n",
    "        if label in selected_genre_labels:\n",
    "            query_vec[i] = genre_weight\n",
    "    query_vec[-1] = (1 - genre_weight)  # assume max rating for query\n",
    "    matrix = build_feature_matrix(df_in, genre_cols, genre_weight)\n",
    "    sims = cosine_similarity([query_vec], matrix)[0]\n",
    "    sim_scores = sorted(enumerate(sims), key=lambda x: x[1], reverse=True)[:top_n]\n",
    "    recs = df_in.iloc[[i for i, _ in sim_scores]][['anime','rate','votes','episodes']].copy()\n",
    "    recs['similarity_%'] = [round(s * 100, 2) for _, s in sim_scores]\n",
    "    return recs.reset_index(drop=True)"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "id": "c7",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": ["### 3.2 Demo: Recommend by Title"]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": null,
   "id": "c8",
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "title_query = 'Naruto Shippuuden'\n",
    "recs_title = recommend_by_title(title_query, df_model, matrix_07, GENRE_COLS, top_n=10)\n",
    "print(f'Recommendations similar to: {title_query}')\n",
    "display(recs_title.style.background_gradient(subset=['similarity_%'], cmap='plasma'))"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "id": "c9",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": ["### 3.3 Demo: Recommend by Genres"]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": null,
   "id": "c10",
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "genre_query = ['Action', 'Fantasy', 'Shonen']\n",
    "recs_genre = recommend_by_genres(genre_query, df_model, GENRE_COLS, GENRE_LABELS, genre_weight=0.7, top_n=10)\n",
    "print(f'Recommendations for genres: {genre_query}')\n",
    "display(recs_genre.style.background_gradient(subset=['similarity_%'], cmap='plasma'))"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "id": "d1",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": ["## 4. Effect of Genre Weight Parameter"]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": null,
   "id": "d2",
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "# Compare how genre_weight affects recommendations for 'Sword Art Online'\n",
    "title_test = 'Sword Art Online'\n",
    "weights = [1.0, 0.7, 0.5]\n",
    "\n",
    "for w in weights:\n",
    "    m = build_feature_matrix(df_model, GENRE_COLS, genre_weight=w)\n",
    "    r = recommend_by_title(title_test, df_model, m, GENRE_COLS, top_n=5)\n",
    "    print(f'\\n--- genre_weight={w} ---')\n",
    "    display(r[['anime','rate','similarity_%']])"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "id": "e1",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "## 5. Key Takeaways\n",
    "\n",
    "- The dataset contains **1,255 anime** from Crunchyroll with **28 pre-encoded genre columns** — no tokenization needed.\n",
    "- **566 anime** pass the minimum 50-vote quality filter, forming the active recommendation pool.\n",
    "- The weighted cosine similarity approach balances **genre relevance (70%)** and **rating quality (30%)** by default, tuneable via the `genre_weight` slider in the Streamlit app.\n",
    "- Genre co-occurrence analysis reveals that **Action + Adventure + Shonen** and **Romance + Drama + Comedy** are the most common multi-genre clusters.\n",
    "- Purely genre-based (weight=1.0) recommendations tend to be more niche; adding the rating signal (weight=0.7) surfaces more well-known quality titles.\n"
   ]
  }
 ]
}
